  "prompt": "How do you get over someone you never were in a relationship with?",
  "response": "Getting over someone you never officially dated can be challenging. Here are some helpful strategies:\n\n1. Acknowledge your feelings\n- Validate that your emotions are real\n- Accept that these feelings are valid, even if the relationship wasn't official\n\n2. Create distance\n- Limit or stop contact with the person\n- Unfollow or mute them on social media\n- Avoid places where you might run into them\n\n3. Practice self-care\n- Focus on your personal growth\n- Exercise and maintain a healthy lifestyle\n- Pursue hobbies and interests\n- Spend time with supportive friends and family\n\n4. Process your emotions\n- Journal your thoughts and feelings\n- Talk to trusted friends\n- Consider talking to a therapist\n- Allow yourself to grieve the potential relationship\n\n5. Reframe your perspective\n- Recognize that the relationship wasn't meant to be\n- Understand that you deserve someone who fully reciprocates your feelings\n- Learn from the experience\n\n6. Stay busy and distracted\n- Try new activities\n- Meet new people\n- Set personal and professional goals\n- Invest time in self-improvement\n\n7. Be patient with yourself\n- Healing takes time\n- Don't rush the process\n- Be kind to yourself during emotional recovery\n\nRemember that healing is a personal journey, and everyone processes emotions differently.",
